Ironically the only two comedy sequels I can think of that were any good were Waynes World and Austin Powers (and Jackass 2 if you want to count that). With Mike Meyers recent track record, its very surprising he was the one to pull off two great comedy sequels.  Comedy sequels are just giant cash grabs 99% hopefully this will be in the 1%. Broken Lizard's team seems to have made the HUGE blunder of mistakenly taking the French culture (From France) and applying it to the French Canadians (Quebecers), which is VERY different in terms of accent, attitude and LOTS of other factors. I SINCERELY hope it's only shown as such cause those cops are really dumb and the joke will be on them, otherwise it'll display an incredible lack of laziness in term of research especially since doing an actual movie which plays alot with the culture clash concept.... I'm quite inclined to believe the latter cause this confusion would not be the first time... Please Super Trooper team, show me you are not actual real idiots! Cause I really enjoyed the first one!
